            "title": "Former SEC Chair Gary Gensler defended agency's stance on cryptocurrencies, highlighting investor protection, cites crypto as risky due to hype and fraud cases.",
            "id": "55c3627a-edb5-4a00-9a0b-b058c16b71ea",
            "description": "Former SEC Chair Gary Gensler affirmed the agency's regulatory stance on cryptocurrencies, emphasizing its focus on \"investor protection.\" In an interview with CNBC, Gensler defended his decisions during his tenure, contrasting them with the pro-cryptocurrency actions taken by current chair Paul Atkins. Gensler acknowledged the importance of safeguarding investors and cited prominent cryptocurrency fraud cases, such as the Sam Bankman-Fried incident. He described the crypto market as driven by momentum and investor hype, labeling it as a \"risky\" asset. Gensler's remarks underscore the challenges and complexities surrounding cryptocurrencies and the need for regulatory oversight to protect investors.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/55c3627a-edb5-4a00-9a0b-b058c16b71ea",
